Have you ever visited fairy tale building Casa Batlló? 🧚‍♀️
.
Casa Batlló is one of the two great buildings designed by Antoni Gaudí. From the outside the façade of Casa Batlló looks like it has been made from skulls and bones. The "Skulls" are in fact balconies and the "bones" are supporting pillars. Gaudí used colours and shapes found in marine life as inspiration for his creativity in this building.
Location: Barcelona, Spain 🇪🇸 Photo by @teainasuitcase 👍
.
